WEBVTT

00:46.305 --> 00:47.468
Robin.

00:48.724 --> 00:50.006
Look at me, Robin.

00:54.272 --> 00:56.727
Do you believe when I say I love you?

00:58.025 --> 01:00.778
How long has this been going on?

01:01.404 --> 01:03.563
24 years? 25?

01:04.239 --> 01:06.197
I've always been there for you.

01:06.534 --> 01:08.740
Always, in any situation.

01:09.162 --> 01:12.246
To all your... choices, all your fears...

01:12.832 --> 01:13.829
all that...

01:14.625 --> 01:17.959
enslavement here, anxieties, I was there.

01:18.812 --> 01:20.588
All the irrational walkouts,

01:21.132 --> 01:24.300
always when... shooting was
just about to start.

01:24.552 --> 01:27.180
"Do me a favor, Al, get me out of this,
get me out of that".

01:27.263 --> 01:28.639
"Get me out clean",

01:28.723 --> 01:30.639
"without burning any bridges".

01:31.893 --> 01:33.969
"Aaron needs me at home."

01:36.022 --> 01:38.062
But Aaron is just an excuse.

01:39.984 --> 01:41.714
Lousy choices.

01:42.987 --> 01:45.360
That's your whole story, Robin.

01:45.894 --> 01:47.444
Lousy choices.

01:48.160 --> 01:49.743
Lousy movies,

01:50.011 --> 01:52.948
lousy men, friends you couldn't trust.

01:53.299 --> 01:55.204
Even the one thing you can't choose,

01:55.288 --> 01:56.288
your mother.

01:57.376 --> 01:59.156
You made a lousy choice there, too.

02:00.637 --> 02:02.074
You had it all, Robin.

02:03.857 --> 02:06.166
Movie queen at 24.

02:06.987 --> 02:09.484
All the big studios came crawling.

02:13.267 --> 02:15.240
Maybe I was too soft on you...

02:16.536 --> 02:17.790
like everyone says.

02:20.358 --> 02:21.473
I don't know.

02:23.569 --> 02:25.277
Maybe I really was.

02:27.738 --> 02:29.295
But you were just a kid.

02:30.271 --> 02:31.489
You were scared.

02:31.702 --> 02:34.076
You made that choices,
you made them all on your own.

02:34.372 --> 02:36.448
And you slammed all the open doors,

02:36.666 --> 02:38.187
crushed all the dreams.

02:40.711 --> 02:41.791
And now...

02:44.048 --> 02:44.961
Now...

02:46.261 --> 02:47.579
And now what, Al?

02:48.732 --> 02:50.761
Talk to me, what are they offering?

02:51.248 --> 02:54.140
I've no idea that they offer,
I wish I knew.

02:54.350 --> 02:56.602
They called this morning
and yelled at me for 20 minutes,

02:56.825 --> 02:58.477
about how they're sick of us.

02:58.688 --> 03:00.381
Said it was a "final offer",

03:01.145 --> 03:02.935
that this proposal won't be on the table again.

03:04.159 --> 03:06.654
A quotation: "That won't be on the table again."

03:06.863 --> 03:08.342
And what do you think it is?

03:08.426 --> 03:10.066
How on Earth would I know?

03:10.950 --> 03:13.592
One thing I do know: they won't be back.

03:15.413 --> 03:17.821
They never spoke to me that way, Robin.

03:18.036 --> 03:18.893
Ever.

03:19.584 --> 03:21.878
Sorry of that, Mom.
I think you need to go now.

03:21.961 --> 03:22.709
What happened?

03:23.004 --> 03:25.424
Airport security called. No pressure,
same as usual.

03:56.755 --> 03:57.575
Aaron!

04:32.423 --> 04:34.613
That's right. The next time the
kite goes over property fence,

04:34.696 --> 04:35.827
- you know what's gonna happen.
- I know.

04:36.035 --> 04:37.992
I know, I'm sorry,
it's not going to happen again.

05:06.941 --> 05:08.353
So what was that Aaron?

05:08.568 --> 05:11.023
United 435 from Rochester?

05:12.238 --> 05:13.401
Actually, no.

05:14.740 --> 05:16.257
- What was it then?
- Um...

05:16.576 --> 05:18.595
United... but not Rochester.

05:19.078 --> 05:19.996
Let's see...

05:20.079 --> 05:22.546
Wednesday, 6 p.m.

05:23.457 --> 05:24.620
Fort Lauderdale?

05:26.002 --> 05:27.200
I know, Minneapolis.

05:29.881 --> 05:32.585
- That's not what matters.
- What matters then?

05:35.428 --> 05:37.587
That the wind was blowing from the west,

05:38.910 --> 05:41.776
that my lady flew like a Queen
over the runways...

05:41.976 --> 05:44.349
and that it looked like a match made in Heaven.

05:46.167 --> 05:48.184
I thought that any minute
they were gonna unite.

05:49.066 --> 05:50.312
Those colors!

05:50.860 --> 05:51.809
That red,

05:52.195 --> 05:53.143
that white

05:53.738 --> 05:55.197
and the black clouds.

05:57.404 --> 05:58.571
So really powerful.

05:58.654 --> 05:59.983
OK, but guess what?

06:00.066 --> 06:02.095
It's not gonna happen anymore,
you know that, right?

06:02.288 --> 06:03.137
Why not, why do you care?

06:03.162 --> 06:05.606
Because he's not gonna go there,
that's why it's not gonna happen.

06:07.035 --> 06:09.675
All right? Because the next time
the line goes over the fence,

06:09.758 --> 06:11.445
we're gonna have to pack
everything in the house

06:11.714 --> 06:13.707
we're gonna have to move to
a lousy neighborhood in the city,

06:13.925 --> 06:16.135
where there will be no sky for you to see, or kites.

06:16.219 --> 06:19.007
I'd rather live in some lousy neighborhood
in the city than this shit.

06:19.806 --> 06:21.217
Oh, that's not new.

06:23.976 --> 06:25.493
You know, I saved you today.

06:26.145 --> 06:27.059
You saved me? From what?

06:27.522 --> 06:28.933
From Al's proposal.

06:29.565 --> 06:31.118
What was he offering so sweetly?

06:35.530 --> 06:36.277
Tell her, Mom.

06:36.572 --> 06:39.277
- What did he offer?
- I DON'T know, I don't know.

06:39.784 --> 06:41.503
Sci-Fi? Graphic novel?

06:41.587 --> 06:44.154
Holocaust? I don't see WHY you won't
do a Holocaust flick?

06:44.539 --> 06:47.203
Every B-grade actress that does Holocaust
wins something in.

06:48.167 --> 06:49.994
You could play both sides.

06:50.211 --> 06:51.243
What do you mean, both sides?

06:51.546 --> 06:53.123
Well, look at you.

06:53.708 --> 06:55.937
Nazi and victim.

06:56.676 --> 06:58.621
You're multi-purpose
for a Holocaust flick.

06:59.220 --> 07:00.349
- You know what?
- What?

07:00.433 --> 07:03.352
You could even play a collaborator
if they needed one.

07:03.436 --> 07:06.268
How many actresses have THAT
kind of talent these days?

07:44.637 --> 07:48.267
Yeah, I remember. I remember when you
first came to the studio.

07:48.478 --> 07:50.646
I was a... young number-cruncher,

07:50.730 --> 07:51.892
down the hall.

07:52.783 --> 07:54.461
Everybody said: "Here she comes!"

07:54.544 --> 07:56.816
"She is beautiful, she is sexy,

07:56.899 --> 07:59.739
She's got brains, power and ability

07:59.822 --> 08:02.133
modesty, wildness, fantasy."

08:06.496 --> 08:08.748
And she's one of us, goddamn it, she's...

08:08.831 --> 08:10.114
She's from Texas!"

08:11.626 --> 08:15.754
She's not some-some... some actress
that comes from the middle of Australia

08:15.963 --> 08:17.755
that grew up on some distant farm,

08:17.838 --> 08:20.670
that she rode a hundred miles
to get to closest movie

08:20.885 --> 08:23.294
where the projector runs on bunker fuel!

08:25.765 --> 08:28.600
I remember, standing in the hallway...

08:29.018 --> 08:30.726
watching you walk in.

08:30.937 --> 08:32.808
And you were so beautiful.

08:34.398 --> 08:37.229
You were "Princess Bride"... Buttercup.

08:38.820 --> 08:42.318
I imagined switching your face
for that of Grace Kelly's,

08:42.532 --> 08:45.221
in the "Rear Window" poster. That was a good idea.

08:46.619 --> 08:47.956
You were the future, Robin.

08:48.955 --> 08:51.280
You were the promise, the answer.

08:52.083 --> 08:53.910
You were the whole package.

08:56.754 --> 08:57.952
And now I'm...

08:59.257 --> 09:01.167
I'm in this situation.

09:02.051 --> 09:04.257
Exactly what situation are you in, Jeff?

09:05.054 --> 09:08.341
The situation of offering you the last contract
that you'll ever have.

09:10.613 --> 09:11.764
The last?

09:12.186 --> 09:14.227
Already? I'm not even 45.

09:14.522 --> 09:16.432
Things are changing quickly.

09:17.316 --> 09:20.935
Very soon, this whole structure
we all love so much...

09:21.154 --> 09:22.352
will be gone.

09:22.572 --> 09:24.316
What's... Miramount?

09:26.742 --> 09:27.618
God forbid!

09:28.286 --> 09:30.304
I mean the structure around the actor:

09:30.590 --> 09:32.278
the agents, the managers,

09:32.498 --> 09:33.993
all the trappings, the trailer

09:34.208 --> 09:36.961
the drugs, the Coke, the depression, the...

09:37.170 --> 09:40.131
breakups, the lovers, the sexual kinks,

09:40.214 --> 09:41.543
the broken contracts,

09:41.757 --> 09:44.485
the terrible legitimization of tasteless scripts,

09:44.569 --> 09:47.638
the post-failure blues, the skipping out on PR

09:47.722 --> 09:49.549
begging for forgiveness.

09:49.765 --> 09:51.749
All that... can be gone.

09:56.583 --> 09:57.660
Get my drift?

09:58.733 --> 10:00.192
No, not really.

10:03.988 --> 10:05.787
We at Miramount, want to...

10:06.532 --> 10:07.786
want to scan you.

10:08.409 --> 10:12.038
All of you... your body, your face,
your... emotion,

10:12.246 --> 10:15.958
your laughter, your tears,
your climaxing, your happiness,

10:16.042 --> 10:20.196
your depressions, your... fears, longings.

10:21.631 --> 10:25.453
We want to sample you, we
want to preserve you, we want...

10:25.885 --> 10:27.261
all this, this...

10:27.345 --> 10:29.421
this thing, this thing called...

10:30.181 --> 10:31.090
"Robin Wright".

10:34.779 --> 10:37.012
What will you do with this... thing?

10:37.438 --> 10:38.938
That you call Robin Wright?

10:39.440 --> 10:42.387
Will do all the things that
your Robin Wright wouldn't do.

10:43.694 --> 10:44.450
Like what?

10:45.363 --> 10:47.722
Like all the movies that you missed out on

10:47.806 --> 10:49.700
because of your LOUSY choices.

10:49.784 --> 10:52.286
You gave in, you gave up, you fled, you quit,

10:52.370 --> 10:53.912
God knows what you did!

10:53.995 --> 10:55.575
And you did it the last minute,

10:55.658 --> 10:58.649
you clogged our productions
and you cost us MILLIONS!

11:03.339 --> 11:04.206
How old are you?

11:06.217 --> 11:09.116
What difference does it make how old I am,
if you're gonna create

11:09.413 --> 11:13.422
me at any age at your computer! What difference
does it make to you if I am 16 or 60?

11:13.641 --> 11:14.401
It doesn't.

11:15.367 --> 11:18.435
I need Buttercup from "Princess Bride".

11:19.063 --> 11:21.303
I need Jenny from "Forrest Gump."

11:21.386 --> 11:23.266
I need a... what was her name,

11:23.350 --> 11:25.238
from "A State Of Grace"?

11:25.321 --> 11:27.127
That's what I need, I don't need you.

11:29.198 --> 11:31.239
I need you only for your... for your history.

11:31.576 --> 11:34.385
A history paid with lousy choices
you just said so yourself.

11:34.468 --> 11:36.959
Yes. For the last 15 years, yes, sure.

11:37.043 --> 11:39.171
All your movies tanked, no-not one...

11:39.474 --> 11:40.955
could keep it's head above water.

11:42.044 --> 11:45.140
But I can save you, Robin.
I can save you.

11:45.897 --> 11:49.040
- From what?
- From yourself! From yourself!

11:53.598 --> 11:54.760
You knew about this?

11:56.350 --> 11:57.050
Knew about what?

11:57.351 --> 11:59.173
About all this crap he's offering me?

11:59.353 --> 12:03.349
Oh, he doesn't know anything, he still thinks
that cameras run on bunker fuel.

12:05.318 --> 12:06.017
On what?

12:06.444 --> 12:08.246
A bunker fuel, that's crude oil.

12:08.558 --> 12:10.770
Never mind. He is from the Stone Age.

12:15.703 --> 12:17.530
Your career is almost over.

12:18.372 --> 12:20.982
You fell off the Top-O.

12:22.556 --> 12:24.730
In the economy of scanned actors, um...

12:25.880 --> 12:28.205
you're not worth... 2 bucks.

12:29.926 --> 12:31.503
We're at war, Robin.

12:31.803 --> 12:35.854
Any actor who doesn't sign within
the next 6 months is dead. Gone.

12:36.599 --> 12:39.268
Characters erased from the screen forever.

12:41.479 --> 12:43.852
You'll be back on all fours,

12:44.065 --> 12:45.632
begging me to sample you.

12:49.403 --> 12:51.729
What is it that I have to do
to make that happen?

12:51.889 --> 12:52.497
Nothing.

12:54.367 --> 12:55.695
Just sign.

12:55.910 --> 12:56.740
Half a day of scanning.

12:57.078 --> 12:58.703
- That's it?
- That's it.

12:59.288 --> 13:01.958
That and... you must agree to never act again.

13:02.500 --> 13:04.825
Anywhere for all eternity.

13:06.796 --> 13:08.255
What do you mean, "anywhere"?

13:08.881 --> 13:11.509
No movies, no TV show,

13:11.592 --> 13:14.428
no school plays, no French theater

13:14.512 --> 13:15.793
in Western Australia?

13:15.877 --> 13:17.761
"Anywhere" means Anywhere.

13:20.643 --> 13:23.415
Robin Wright The Actress will live and breathe...

13:23.498 --> 13:25.972
within the walls of Miramount Studios.

13:27.215 --> 13:29.982
And this Robin Wright can take the money

13:30.192 --> 13:33.030
and fly off to some island in Polynesia

13:33.114 --> 13:34.739
to discover her true self.

13:37.792 --> 13:38.953
Whadda you say?

13:42.415 --> 13:44.222
You know, it's interesting. Um...

13:44.858 --> 13:46.757
We actresses used to talk about how we never

13:46.840 --> 13:48.840
wanted to sleep with you for a part
in the movie, but

13:48.923 --> 13:51.239
but you know what? Honestly, I think
I'd rather do that...

13:51.942 --> 13:54.503
than be a fucking chip in your computer, Jeff.

13:56.637 --> 13:57.800
So, thanks.

13:58.556 --> 13:59.635
But, no thanks.

14:08.024 --> 14:09.815
The offer is valid for 30 days.

14:10.026 --> 14:11.215
After that, she's on her own.

14:34.760 --> 14:36.343
How do you feel, sweetie?

14:46.979 --> 14:48.261
What's up?

14:55.638 --> 14:57.364
I was tired, I guess.

14:58.908 --> 15:01.338
You want to try and fly the Wright brothers' glider?

15:03.136 --> 15:05.244
No... she's not ready yet.

15:05.498 --> 15:07.455
So maybe one of the Cody's?

15:10.211 --> 15:11.457
I don't know.

15:17.718 --> 15:19.292
I missed the 2 o'clock landing.

15:24.225 --> 15:25.423
What's wrong?

15:28.271 --> 15:30.291
You look... you look sad.

15:30.754 --> 15:31.962
- Really?
- Yeah.

15:36.529 --> 15:38.819
Why don't you fly one of Cody Bank's?

15:39.490 --> 15:40.540
- Me?
- Yeah.

15:40.741 --> 15:42.948
- I don't think so.
- You can do it.

15:44.745 --> 15:46.027
Just the little one.

15:47.582 --> 15:48.697
Come on.

15:49.584 --> 15:51.992
You better try it for once, alone.

15:53.004 --> 15:54.534
Gotta see what it feels like.

15:57.466 --> 15:59.009
I'll be there and watch your line,

16:00.052 --> 16:01.367
so it doesn't go over that fence.

16:03.431 --> 16:05.382
Don't want to get kicked out of this place, do we?

17:15.837 --> 17:17.117
Sarah, get it.

17:17.380 --> 17:18.292
Me?

17:18.506 --> 17:20.381
Did you ever see someone come to visit me here?

17:20.633 --> 17:22.045
Right, here, hold this.

17:31.853 --> 17:33.229
It's okay.

17:37.278 --> 17:38.442
You could call.

17:38.526 --> 17:40.676
What good would that have done?
You haven't answered my calls

17:40.759 --> 17:42.189
since the meeting at the studio.

17:42.655 --> 17:46.325
This is Steve. He'll draw up
your contract with the studio.

17:46.409 --> 17:48.200
He's a scanning contract genius.

17:48.411 --> 17:51.002
Keanu Reeves, Michelle Williams...
he did their contracts.

17:51.289 --> 17:53.163
They're hermetically scanned.

17:55.030 --> 17:56.658
Nice to meet you.

17:57.086 --> 17:58.284
Hi, kids!

18:06.596 --> 18:08.553
- You want a drink, Al?
- Sure.

18:08.764 --> 18:11.119
- Would you like a drink?
- No, thank you.

18:16.147 --> 18:18.074
- It's a real glider.
- Yeah.

18:18.858 --> 18:21.100
Thank you, this is... this is beautiful.

18:27.241 --> 18:28.353
And who is this?

18:29.285 --> 18:32.330
This is Steve, a new lawyer I'm working with.

18:32.413 --> 18:34.119
Scanning contract genius.

18:34.202 --> 18:37.767
This is one hell of a warehouse
you guys have here.

18:38.044 --> 18:39.705
Oh no, it's not a warehouse.

18:39.921 --> 18:42.424
It's an old hangar for the DC-9s.

18:42.508 --> 18:44.130
It was built in like 1973.

18:44.213 --> 18:47.780
Wow! I mean, you could NEVER get
a 17 GPC permit

18:47.863 --> 18:50.761
to do a residential conversion like this
these days, that's for sure.

18:51.766 --> 18:53.676
Scanning genius, eh?

18:54.227 --> 18:56.729
Well, I've happen to have seen
on the entertainment channel that

18:56.813 --> 19:01.180
studios are starting to sample actors
into these tiny little computer creatures.

19:01.400 --> 19:04.070
I mean, it must change the way
contracting works, completely.

19:04.153 --> 19:06.237
It's absolutely true, uh...

19:06.320 --> 19:08.340
- Sarah.
- Yes, that's absolutely true, Sarah,

19:08.423 --> 19:10.925
is a completely different type of contracts,
it's a one-off sale.

19:11.369 --> 19:13.973
Very tricky, lots of details and you have to be sharp.

19:14.163 --> 19:16.349
- 'Cause it's not going back to fix it afterwards.
- Uh-huh.

19:16.874 --> 19:18.548
What do you mean by "one-off sale"?

19:19.126 --> 19:21.962
Once they sample you, and you're in the computer
there is no way back.

19:22.171 --> 19:24.662
So whatever was agreed before
the sampling... that's the way it is.

19:24.882 --> 19:26.676
So you have to be really careful.

19:26.759 --> 19:28.508
The studio owns the character.

19:28.845 --> 19:31.135
- W-What character?
- One that used to be the actor.

19:31.305 --> 19:32.110
"Used to be"?

19:32.194 --> 19:35.886
The minute the studio pays and scans,
the actor isn't an actor,

19:36.102 --> 19:38.177
He's just a person, a nobody.

19:38.771 --> 19:41.660
The actor he once was
is now on a character

19:41.744 --> 19:42.866
in the studio's computer.

19:42.914 --> 19:44.058
The studio can do whatever they want.

19:44.277 --> 19:47.195
Unless the lawyer puts a clause in,
saying that they can't some.

19:47.405 --> 19:49.050
It's very tricky.

19:49.245 --> 19:50.240
Very tricky.

19:50.962 --> 19:53.137
It's a new field. We're on the cusp.

19:53.911 --> 19:56.284
- So what happens to the actor?
- What actor?

19:57.043 --> 20:00.207
The one that used to be the actor
is now this... computer creature.

20:01.210 --> 20:03.701
He goes off to play golf somewhere.

20:04.213 --> 20:05.560
And what if he doesn't like golf?

20:07.608 --> 20:10.380
Well then he plays... with whatever.

20:10.782 --> 20:12.470
Do you have a screen in this house?

20:12.680 --> 20:14.839
Or is that too progressive for you, guys?

20:19.228 --> 20:21.898
You know what, there's something else
I haven't told you.

20:23.119 --> 20:26.184
- Oh yeah? What is it? What haven't you told me?
- Yeah.

20:26.474 --> 20:29.237
They will be in 15 minutes, so, get it out. What?

20:31.918 --> 20:33.159
Oh my God...

20:34.327 --> 20:35.899
You were with Maria, too.

20:36.496 --> 20:38.655
Oh, say it, you piece of shit.

20:38.943 --> 20:40.085
Say you were with her, too.

20:40.583 --> 20:42.244
I knew that, honey,
I knew it the whole time.

20:42.327 --> 20:44.085
Where that little slut seduces you out...

20:45.600 --> 20:48.868
Oh my God, Max... Max! It makes me wanna vomit.

20:48.952 --> 20:51.790
- No, I wasn't with Maria.
- Oh, no? NO?!

20:51.969 --> 20:54.013
- Well, then who?
- I wasn't with anybody.

20:54.096 --> 20:55.212
But...

20:58.068 --> 20:59.511
I voted for Bush.

21:08.903 --> 21:10.313
You voted for Bush?

21:10.530 --> 21:13.519
I voted for Bush. You know what,
I voted for both Bushes,

21:13.602 --> 21:15.189
senior and junior,

21:15.608 --> 21:16.796
four times!

21:22.166 --> 21:23.080
Who are you?

21:24.674 --> 21:27.402
Oh my God, who did I marry? Sweetie-sweetie...

21:32.135 --> 21:33.842
That isn't Michelle.

21:34.137 --> 21:35.632
That is Michelle!

21:36.266 --> 21:38.470
No, I mean, obviously it's Michelle, but...

21:39.016 --> 21:41.472
you telling me she wasn't there
when they did this?

21:41.555 --> 21:46.402
You really want to know? She was in Paris when
they were making that crap on their computers.

